            # content if desired
            docstrings.append([])
        for i, line in enumerate(self.process_doc(docstrings)):
            self.add_line(line, sourcename, i)
```

When `docstrings` is `[]`, it appends `[]` to it, making it `[[]]`. Then `process_doc` yields from it, which yields nothing (empty list). So nothing is added. Then `more_content` is added, which contains "alias of ...".

So if `get_doc()` returns `[]`, only "alias of ..." is shown. If `get_doc()` returns the docstring, both the docstring and "alias of ..." are shown.

